# The @kawasekit scope (the private mpc-2p client) lives on the GitHub Packages
# registry, NOT public npm — it ships with your owner-hosted co-signer. Public
# packages (kawasekit, hono, viem, …) still come from npmjs.
#
# This file only maps the scope to the registry (no secret, no env reference — so a
# token-less `pnpm install` is clean: `@kawasekit/mpc-2p` is an OPTIONAL dependency
# and is simply excluded, while the metered-API server installs and runs for anyone).
#
# To install the private client, authenticate to GitHub Packages with a token that has
# `read:packages` (+ access to the kawasekit org packages), e.g. once per machine:
#   npm config set //npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken "$GITHUB_TOKEN"
@kawasekit:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
